                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18141130-76-victim783 t18141130-76-viclabel466"></join>, at Hackney.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you lose any shoes at any time - A. Yes, at the latter end of October I missed a pair of shoes, and on the second day that she was in the house, I missed another pair of shoes. When my servant went away, the prisoner was recommended to me during her absence; and on the 22d of November, I missed another pair of shoes. I then suspected the prisoner; she left my house on Monday evening; she left my house and went to her lodging; my servant had returned. I immediately went to the prisoner's lodging, suspecting that she might be the person that took the shoes. I begged her to give my property up; she denied having it; an officer was fetched; the three pair of shoes was found in the cupboard; these are the shoes; they are my property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am innocent of the charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18141130-76-verdict467" type="verdictDescription">
